Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Hey, this is a short summary about Lympo. You are always welcome to read our full whitepaper: https://lympo.io/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/whitepaper.pdf?v5  Lympo.io is a healthy lifestyle ecosystem powered by user-generated user-controlled sports and wellness data. Lympo users will be able to connect their favourite health apps and wearables to their Lympo digital fitness wallet and earn LYM tokens for being healthy through challenges organised by fitness trainers, gyms, sports events, employees or health insurers. LYM tokens can be further used to buy other healthy lifestyle goods and services. Furthermore, Lympo users will be able to monetize their valuable data giving access to it to a number of stakeholders in the ecosystem: gyms, sports apparel producers, health insurances, data driven companies. Access permissions stored on blockchain will offer a unique service to companies in the world of tightening data protection rules. Putting this valuable data in the hands of users producing it will allow a seamless precious data flow for the benefit of all healthy lifestyle stakeholders. In the future, the tokens will also be used to invest in the most promising companies in the industry which aim to utilize the data of Lympo users.

Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain

Please read more about how Lympo complies with the EU General Data Protection Regulations: https://medium.com/@lympo.io/lympo-is-a-step-ahead-in-adopting-the-new-eu-data-regulations-and-abiding-by-it-596c26a79c07.

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Let's separate two ways of using the platform here: 1. the phase of data aggregation 2. the phase of data monetization.  Obviously, to monetize data you have to have aggregated it on the platform.  Ways to do that (2 examples): A. to book online/offline personal training sessions and get rewards for the achieved fitness and mindfulness goals. In this case rewards work more like a cash back: you pay for a training in LYM tokens and if you reach the goals on which you decide together with your trainer, you get tokens in reward, a proportion of the tokens paid for the training session.  B. to participate in various challenges by our partners. E.g. an athletic shoe producer wants to promote the brand. The company purchases some LYM tokens and announces a running challenge: all those who run at least 5 km this week, will get some tokens as a reward. A Lympo user runs 5 km, submits the data to the system and gets tokens in return.

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Hey thetractor666, Lympo can be used by the athletes, but its main goal is to make everyone profit. How can you benefit from that?  1. If you have a smartphone with any sports/health app on it, like Runkeeper, Endomondo or any other popular app, OR a wearable like Fitbit, you are producing a lot of valuable data: the kilometers you walk or run everyday, maybe you measure your heart rate, your sleeping rhythm, maybe you have a diet app and follow your diet.  2. This valuable data is now being stored with the provider of the app/wearable. They aggregate all this data, do big data analysis, use it after putting a layer of anonymity for interacting with other providers, use it for marketing etc.  3. What do you get from that? Nothing. Except that you can see yourself how many kilometers you just walked and share it on social media.  4. With Lympo you will be able to aggregate this data, get rewards for achieved healthy lifestyle goals (let's say a popular shoe producer makes a 5km running challenge for marketing purpose and offers some tokens in reward) and then also sell it and receive micropayments in LYM tokens.  5. Furthermore, companies that want to use your data and if you decide to sell it, can register your permission to access this data on blockchain. That helps them a lot in making sure that they are compliant with data protection regulations.  6. Now what can you do with these tokens? I. You can use them in the marketplace and get further products or services. II. You can invest them in the most promising health/sports/fitness startups on Lympo crowdfunding platform!

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Hey adotrulez! A spot on question. Let me quote the security measures we are planning to have in place: We believe that security is key for our users and therefore we got one of the best security experts we could find as our advisor: Hainan Hu, formerly Zalando and Sound Cloud, now Boston Consulting Group Digital Ventures: https://www.linkedin.com/in/hainan/. One of the data storage solutions we are looking at are HIPPA compliant AWS services. The other solution is developed by the former company of our advisor Dr. David Manset, Gnubila: https://www.fedehr.com/. Now, both FedEHR and HIPPA compliant AWS services are meant to be protecting electronic medical records. The information Lympo will be working with, the data from health and sports tracking apps, is not qualified to be as sensitive as medical health records, but we still prefer to use one of these solutions to make sure that in the future our users could store their medical records as well.  Our team is group of people who are hard working and want to reach the best results possible. It is not a new team gathered for this token sale only. Most of the team members have been working together for more than a year now to release www.lympo.lt, a platform to find the best personal trainer in Lithuania, currently expanding to California. This team will go on building great products and, most importantly, having the expertise in fitness, sports and health sectors which is crucial to build something really useful of our community.

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Thank you! In comparison to many other blockchain for healthcare projects, Lympo does not aim to collect or store electronic medical records, because we believe that it is still too early and the technology needs to gain more trust from institutions and patients. However, we want to make sure that all of us who gather health/sports/wellness data on our phone apps or wearables, are rewarded for this valuable data we provide about ourselves. While we are not offering a new app, Lympo proposes a way to collect and monetise this data with the user controlling it.

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: We are proud to present  LYMPO.IO MONETIZING SPORTS AND HEALTH DATA VIA BLOCKCHAIN HEALTHY LIFESTYLE ECOSYSTEM POWERED BY USER-GENERATED AND USER-CONTROLLED SPORTS AND WELLNESS DATA  Translations: Arabic translation Hindi translation German translation Indonesian translation Vietnamese translation Chinese translation French translation Spanish translation Russian translation Italian translation Portuguese translation Romanian translation Turkish translation Japanese translation Dutch translation Philippines translation      The usage of mobile health (mHealth) apps and wearables is ever-growing. More than 52% of smart phone users gather health-related information on their phone. In 2016 alone, mHealth app store downloads totalled 3.2 billion.  However, the users generating this data cannot aggregate, share and monetize it. Moreover, because it lacks the means to interconnect existing data, the industry cannot unlock its full potential for the benefit of all market players. The rise of mHealth applications has not yet delivered on the promise of digital technology empowering individuals and resulting in better health care and a more connected sports and wellness market. The Lympo ecosystem resolves this problem. Powered by user-generated and user-controlled fitness and wellness data, Lympo will allow the exchange of value through the introduction LYM utility tokens. Lympo‚Äôs goal is an ecosystem where data is used efficiently by all industry stakeholders and everyone is rewarded fairly. It consists of three pillars: the Lympo fitness wallet, a marketplace and the Lympo crowdfunding platform. The Lympo digital fitness wallet and user reward mechanism is at the core of the Lympo ecosystem. The wallet functions as an entry to the ecosystem and allows users to be rewarded in LYM tokens for their healthy lifestyle achievements. These tokens can be used to purchase goods and services in a marketplace starting from an existing Lympo platform uniting more than 500 fitness professionals and later expanding to a broad network of sports, wellness and health goods and services providers. Finally, LYM tokens will be used on the Lympo crowdfunding platform to invest in innovative data driven companies in the industry which will contribute to the growth of this new ecosystem. Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Hey pikecara! This is a very good question. We believe that security is key for our users and therefore we believe we got one of the best security experts we could find as our advisor: Hainan Hu, formerly Zalando and Sound Cloud, now Boston Consulting Group Digital Ventures: https://www.linkedin.com/in/hainan/. One of the data storage solutions we are looking at are HIPPA compliant AWS services. The other solution is developed by the former company of our advisor Dr. David Manset, Gnubila: https://www.fedehr.com/. Now, both FedEHR and HIPPA compliant AWS services are meant to be protecting electronic medical records. The information Lympo will be working with, the data from health and sports tracking apps, is not qualified to be as sensitive as medical health records, but we still prefer to use one of these solutions to make sure that in the future our users could store their medical records as well.

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: We are focusing on fitness coaches, because Lympo is first and foremost an product that will enable you to get token rewards for a data that you gather on your phone or wearables, like, how many steps you walked today, the heart rhythm etc. I am very happy that a famous Australian holistic health coach and crypto investor who invested in Ethereum ICO Jordan Travers joined Lympo: http://bitcoinist.com/aussie-cryptocurrency-millionaire-investor-jordan-travers-newest-ambassador-blockchain-fitness-app-lympo/.  We have a functioning platform uniting 500+ sports coaches www.lympo.lt (it is only in Lithuanian now) and the platform is currently expanding to California and Melbourne. Our partner Gympro (www.gympro.com) is a company offering a tool for client management for fitness coaches and is currently used by 3000+ coaches in Australia, New Zealand, U.S. and UK.  Having all these community members in mind, we believe that this is how Lympo platform will start taking off.  Ada, CEO Lympo.io

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Hey Heyspongebob! Lympo.io is building a sports and wellness data ecosystem. We believe that any company that is interested in rewarding their users for trackable health goals, can use Lympo rewards mechanism. One of our partners, Smackway www.smackway.com, is a wholesale marketplace for organic and healthy food. Smackway plans to accept payments in LYM tokens in the near future. Our goal is to give our users who collected LYM tokens for being healthy a possibility to purchase further healthy lifestyle products and services.  I am sure that Herbalife could be a great partner for Lympo and we will seek this type of partnerships with the help of the portion of LYM tokens reserved for the ecosystem growth.  Ada, CEO of Lympo.io

Author: LYMPO_health_off
Title: [ANN] [LYM] Lympo - Monetizing sports and health data via blockchain
Body: Hey hesham! I strongly believe that blockchain applications in the financial sector is only a beginning and it will spread to more and more industries. Healthcare is a great example and what we want to do is to allow you to be rewarded for your fitness/sports/health data which you gather on your phone or wearbles. The power of user-controlled data is that it can be shared whenever a user finds it beneficial. Right now, cross-border data sharing, for example, is forbidden (for a good reason), but users controlling their data themselves could make a free data flow beneficial for all possible.
